(
  'Sean Combs — Music Mogul and Federal Sex Trafficking / Racketeering Network',
  'The Sean Combs archive entry centers on Sean Combs (a/k/a "Diddy," "Puff Daddy," "P. Diddy"), founder of Bad Boy Records, and his documented federal prosecution for operating a criminal enterprise involving sex trafficking, forced labor, and related offenses. In September 2024, Combs was indicted in the Southern District of New York. Court records detail a multi-year scheme using his music empire to coerce women into commercial sex acts. He was convicted in 2025 on two counts of transportation to engage in prostitution.',
  E'Documented Evidence Includes:\n\n• Federal indictment (U.S. v. Combs, 1:24-cr-00542) charging racketeering conspiracy, sex trafficking by force/fraud/coercion, and transportation for prostitution.\n• Search warrant returns from March 2024 raids on Combs'' residences documenting "Freak Off" supplies, narcotics, and over 1,000 bottles of baby oil/lubricant.\n• Trial exhibits, victim testimony, travel records, text messages, hotel records, and electronic communications presented in the 2025 Southern District of New York trial.\n• DOJ press releases and sentencing memoranda detailing the enterprise''s use of intimidation, threats, and violence.\n\nThese primary federal court and DOJ materials document elite music-industry networks, coercion, and accountability through prosecution.\n\nThe full case docket is publicly accessible via the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York (PACER) and DOJ archives.\n\nPrimary Sources (MLA Format)\n\nUnited States. Department of Justice. "Sean Combs Charged In Manhattan Federal Court With Sex Trafficking And Other Federal Offenses." 19 Sept. 2024, www.justice.gov/usao-sdny/pr/sean-combs-charged-manhattan-federal-court-sex-trafficking-and-other-federal-offenses.\n\nUnited States v. Combs. United States District Court, Southern District of New York, 1:24-cr-00542 (indictment filed 12 Sept. 2024; unsealed 17 Sept. 2024).\n\nUnited States v. Combs. United States District Court, Southern District of New York, 1:24-cr-00542 (trial verdict and sentencing documents, 2025).',
