  'Marion "Suge" Knight — Death Row Records Founder and Violent Music Industry Network',
  'The Marion "Suge" Knight archive entry centers on the founder of Death Row Records and his multiple criminal convictions tied to the music industry''s violent underbelly, including links to the investigations of Tupac Shakur and The Notorious B.I.G. Knight was convicted of voluntary manslaughter in 2018 for a 2015 hit-and-run and is serving a 28-year sentence under California''s three-strikes law.',
  E'Documented Evidence Includes:\n\n• California Superior Court conviction for voluntary manslaughter (hit-and-run resulting in death).\n• Prior felony convictions and probation violations documented in court records.\n• FBI and LAPD investigative files referencing Knight''s role in Death Row operations and gang-related activities.\n• Sentencing transcripts imposing 28 years under three-strikes provisions.\n\nThese primary state court and law-enforcement records document elite rap-label control, violence, and institutional accountability.\n\nPrimary Sources (MLA Format)\n\nCalifornia. Superior Court of Los Angeles County. People v. Knight (voluntary manslaughter conviction and sentencing, 2018).\n\nUnited States. Federal Bureau of Investigation. Declassified files on Death Row Records investigations (publicly released summaries).',
