  'Duane "Keefe D" Davis — Tupac Shakur Murder Suspect and Gang / Music Industry Network',
  'The Duane "Keefe D" Davis archive entry centers on the self-described former South Side Compton Crips member charged in the 1996 murder of Tupac Shakur. Davis was arrested in 2023 and faces murder charges in Clark County, Nevada. Court filings reference his alleged role in the drive-by shooting outside the MGM Grand.',
  E'Documented Evidence Includes:\n\n• Clark County indictment charging Davis with murder in the death of Tupac Shakur.\n• 2023–2026 court transcripts and motions to suppress evidence from a nighttime search of Davis''s home.\n• Police interview records and grand-jury materials detailing the 1996 events.\n• Trial postponement orders (trial rescheduled to February 2026).\n\nThese primary Nevada court records document long-running investigations into hip-hop''s most infamous unsolved murder and associated gang networks.\n\nPrimary Sources (MLA Format)\n\nNevada. Eighth Judicial District Court, Clark County. State v. Davis, DC No. C-23-377407 (indictment and proceedings, 2023–2026).',
